column5: A friend captured these images and thought the fish was a trout...most definitely not ...but if i was to guess...maybe a mooneye? what do you guys think ??? because im sure as heck am not certain
If i knew how to edit the title i would fix the word "friend"...lol...
Click on edit, then click 'use full editor' and you can change the title.  Not sure what fish it is, but great photos
Nice pics. Definitely not a sucker....most likely a mooneye.
Tough to tell. Mooneye or Gizzard Shad.  Jon
Tough to tell. Mooneye or Gizzard Shad.  Jon  Pretty positive it's a shad.
Yup, hadn't even considered shad but that's even more likely. The anal fin is a giveaway for either unless I'm missing something.

Too big for a mooneye, unless they get bigger than the ones we used to get flyfishing in the Grand or that is a very small Osprey. Shad sounds good. Where are these pictures taken??? that would go a long ways to figuring it out.
pictures were taken at the Bluffers Park  the Osprey was her target to capture....the fish is a bonus! ...Thanks guys..I hadnt considered a Shad either...I was stuck with goldeye and mooneye
Shad (big, wide body), not trout, not mooneye (small, narrow body).
pretty sure its a shad as well
A shad was my first thought too.
well, it's not simcoe herring..cause he would have released it
